@node "PageOne" "Briefing"

       There aren't many Icons in this release, but there are a few that you may like, and I hope
       so! I decided that the old look was good, but then got into making a totaly different look,
       and behold, the new type Drawers (at least) was the result of my tamperings. To be hounest,
       image Drawers are what I like to draw mostely, seeing that I can draw these a lot better...
       You can also tell this because most of the Icons in this "Small" release are mostly Drawer
       Images, wouldn't you think?

       I know I know... who cares eh, just "lemme have the icons and shut up!"?;) I thought so!
       Ok, here is the small lot of Icons I made, and I'll be off now to finnish the rest of this
       Guide file..

       One last thing, you can visualy see whats in the depths of these Drawers, simply click on
       the Visual link here: ( @{" Contents.guide " link contents.guide/main} ) This file was created using Visual Giude

                                   ( Aminet: util/misc/VisualGuide.lha ).

@{" Requester Two " SYSTEM " RUN >NIL: requestchoice The-Briefing This-is-the-update-news-page-please-be-sure-to-read-this-one! Maybe"} Click here for information!  

@{"   Page Two    " link PageTwo} To learn the ways of instalation, click here.

@endnode

@node "PageTwo" "How to install"

       To install these @{b}Images@{ub} simply use the copynewicon utility from the NewIcons46.lha
       from Aminet: ( util/wb/NewIcons46.lha )if you don't have it, get it, or, maybe, you do it a
       different way @{b}without messing anything@{ub} but it's easier using the copynewicon utility,
       unless you have OS35 or so. Your choice however, as long as you know you wont mess anything
       up..just a warning. By now I'm sure there's a lots of easy ways to manipulate Icon images.:-)


@{"  M a i n  " link main}
@endnode
@node "contact" "Contact me will ya?"

       
       Hello folks, it is me, Kevin Hansen, the author of R-R-G_NewIcons Saga 1 and 2!
       I have a new mail since the last time I let stuff go out onto Aminet, and it is
       listed here:
                   
       Kevin Hansen < happycons@home.com >

       I hope you like these new style Icons, and use them like any other icon, but if
       ya don't, thats no biggie! Drawing Icons/Artwork ect, is what I do when I'm not
       lazy which is like ALL the time.. N0T, I'm very lazy! ;)
       
       Ok, I'll stop here before I start typing stuff that doesn't make any sence, so,
       you folks be good, and happy computing!

       Hey wait, these Icons use the same color palette as the previous RPG Icons, so don't
       worry about every icon having a different palette, because they wont have. The new
       wbpatterns (iff brushes) included, also use the same color palette, so don't worry too
       much.
       
